          <Comment>This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Ala2957Cysfs*46) in the PCNT gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in PCNT are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 18174396, 22821869). This variant is present in population databases (rs772244623, gnomAD 0.009%). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with PCNT-related conditions. ClinVar contains an entry for this variant (Variation ID: 159677). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
